# ==(_:_:)

**Operator**

Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two pass error objects are equal.

## Declaration

```swift
static func == (lhs: PKPassKitError, rhs: PKPassKitError) -> Bool
```

## Parameters

- **lhs**: A pass error object to compare.
- **rhs**: Another pass error object to compare.

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/true] if the two errors are equal; otherwise, [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/false]
